      • isAboveWeek

        public boolean isAboveWeek​()
        checks if the unit is month, year or decade.

      • convert

        public double convert​(double measure,
                      GregorianTimeUnit unit)
        converts the given measure from 'this' to unit. Example: 1 minute becomes 3 seconds.
        Parameters:
        measure - any double
        unit - one of the WeightMetric units
        Returns:
        the converted measure or NaN if it cannot be converted.

      • normalize

        public static java.lang.Object[] normalize​(double[] values,
                                           GregorianTimeUnit[] units)
        normalizes a list of value-time units such that they stay within their limits and that they are ordered top-down.
        Example: 5000 days, 500 months becomes: 41.0 year, 8.0 month, 714.0 week, 2.0 day
        months cannot be converted to weeks because they are not synchronous.
        Parameters:
        values - a list of time unit values
        units - the corresponding list of time units
        Returns:
        an array [newValues,timeUnits]

      • parseString

        public static GregorianTimeUnit parseString​(java.lang.String string)
        parses a string into a time unit.
        Parameters:
        string - the string to be parsed.
        Returns:
        one of the predefined time units or null if none can be identified.
